body: I agree that it's quite small. It looks like [`add_queue_runner`](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/training/queue_runner_impl.py#L365) and [`start_queue_runners`](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/training/queue_runner_impl.py#L383) wouldn't be affected. [`QueueRunnerDef`](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/core/protobuf/queue_runner.proto#L17) appears to expect a list of `enqueue_op_name` which breaks from my current use case as the generator performs the enqueue directly.
